WRITING.TITLE: Saturn- Pastel Leopard Ball python 5 months old

WRITING.TEXT: Swap red lights to CHE. stop handling him he hasnt had time to settle if you keep handling him, also sometimes BPs wont eat if they were handled the day before. So leave him alone for a day or two before attempting feed and then 2 days after. Make sure temps are correct they also wont eat if tank temps are off. If it's a glass tank cover the back and sides with cardboard or something to darken the tank, I can't see if you have in those photos. Contact the seller to find out exactly what he was eating. Dont feed mice. Rat chuffs it looks like he'll be on. Make sure the food is heated I use hot water to thaw mine (not boiling you dont want to cook the rat). Could try scenting the rat, worst comes to worst try braining the rat.
